The space for the struggle for the liberation of Guinea Bissau and Cape Verde occurred in the forests and savannas of Guinea Bissau. According to the people's aspiration, Amílcar Cabral, leader of the armed struggle and of the African Party for the Independence of Guinea Bissau and Cape Verde - PAIGC- and ideologue of the independence of the two countries, considers extending the armed struggle to the islands of Cape Verde.
To this end, it begins to mobilize Cape Verdeans scattered throughout the diaspora and forms a group of 31 young people, mostly students, including Pedro Pires, Júlio de Carvalho, Maria Ilidia, and Agnelo Dantas, who decide to embark on an adventure in order to participate in the armed liberation struggle in Cape Verde.
These young people are then sent to Cuba, where they live in complete hiding, and for two years on the island, 1965/67 are subjected to intense military training, with hard hours of guerrilla and artillery training.
With the murder of Che Guevara, the strategy changed and the group ended up not landing in Cape Verde. But, they realized that they could contribute to the liberation of Cape Verde, participating actively in the struggle in Guinea Bissau. Later on, these selfless Creole guerrillas formed the Cape Verdean nation and became influential figures in the country's political life.";s:22:"characters_description";s:1694:"Today, Pedro Pires is the president of Instituto Pedro Pires, an important institution in Cape Verde that promotes leadership training. He was the leader of the Cuba group and even became President of Cape Verde. He is a charismatic figure and considered a historical commander of the national liberation struggle.
Commander Júlio de Carvalho is nowadays a businessman in the trade. He was former Minister of Defense, in the early years of independence he lived in Guinea Bissau and was very dear to the Guinean population and Cubans. At the time of the mobilization, he was studying Chemical Engineering, in Coimbra. He fled Portugal because he had heard that Amílcar Cabral was going to be in Paris. 
Commander Agnelo Dantas, lives the peaceful life of a retired state military officer. He was the youngest of the group, part of Cape Verde at the age of 17, full of revolutionary ideas and to avoid Portuguese military service. His dream was to fight to expel the colonizer from his beloved homeland. After the fight, he was the Chief of Staff of the Armed Forces of Cape Verde.
Maria Ilidia, currently lives in Portugal. She was the only woman in the group. Early on, she begins to realize the differences created by colonialism. It was in the middle of World War II and troops were stationed on the island where she lived, but the Portuguese soldiers and the Cape Verdean soldiers were separated, even the food was different. At the same time she sees her father being beaten and imprisoned, she grows up to fear who had white skin.
In “Nós, Povo das Ilhas” what we are going to do is to enter the intricacies of this bold and daring operation, but little known and publicized.
";s:17:"artistic_approach";s:1979:"How to tell an episode of a country's official history? How to film emblematic and influential figures from Cape Verde, detaching us from the repeated journalistic narratives that build a cold heroic discourse?
We decided to embark on the adventure of telling this episode, using two central elements: the interviews and the archive. When making the teaser we realized that our characters are people very used to the formal interview; and for that reason, when analyzing this material later, we decided that the interviews of the film would be made from a more intimate look. 
We want to interview these characters in their homes, or on the symbolic stages of the war and the early years of independence (today empty spaces and many of them abandoned). Taking these characters to their center, it is a way to return to the core of emotional and emotional memory. We believe that we will reach these non-places of memory, where the characters can question themselves and make themselves known in another way.
To guide this narrative within more personal and intimate space, director Elson Santos will be the narrator that will introduce the “voice” of Cape Verdean youth, who inquires about their past. 
This questioning from a personal perspective will lead the viewer to follow Elson, not only during the interviews with the characters but also in the relentless search for archival material to support this story.
The archival material, which is found only outside Cape Verde (in Portugal, France, and Cuba). The fact that it is so difficult to access the historical memory of a country, is a problem common to all African youth, it will then be an issue that will accompany this archive research. This essayistic and reflective tone will accompany the entire film, as a way of deconstructing the heroic propaganda narratives.
We intend to invite the viewer to question deeply about the value of memory while getting to know the intimate side of all these characters.";s:17:"rel_status_update";s:0:"";s:20:"letter_of_motivation";s:0:"";s:14:"representation";s:0:"";s:21:"representation_upload";s:21:"2021/1618207835_1.jpg";s:16:"contracts_upload";s:0:"";s:15:"artistic_upload";s:0:"";s:13:"visual_upload";s:0:"";s:12:"project_link";s:0:"";s:16:"project_password";s:0:"";s:8:"synopsis";s:0:"";s:13:"projectBudget";s:6:"178615";s:13:"financialPlan";s:0:"";s:12:"totalSecured";s:5:"45405";s:12:"totalApplied";s:1:"0";s:11:"totalPening";s:1:"0";s:13:"BudgetDeficit";s:6:"133210";s:10:"budgetFile";s:21:"2021/1618208905_1.pdf";s:9:"proofFile";s:0:"";s:13:"contractProof";s:0:"";s:12:"ackStatement";s:0:"";s:11:"submittedBy";s:10:"Lara Sousa";s:12:"project_role";s:8:"producer";s:10:"filmmanker";s:0:"";s:8:"producer";s:0:"";s:20:"project_co_ordinator";s:0:"";s:13:"project_role2";s:0:"";s:16:"project_category";s:0:"";s:13:"project_brief";s:0:"";s:16:"project_timeline";s:1:"0";s:16:"project_describe";s:0:"";s:12:"organisation";s:0:"";s:20:"explain_organisation";s:0:"";s:15:"briefly_explain";s:0:"";s:14:"socio_economic";s:0:"";s:10:"video_link";s:0:"";s:16:"description_link";s:0:"";s:20:"description_password";s:0:"";s:15:"proposal_upload";s:0:"";s:10:"project_co";s:1:"0";s:8:"complete";s:1:"1";s:6:"status";s:1:"2";s:5:"addon";s:19:"2021-07-02 20:11:43";s:5:"award";s:1:"0";}i:17;a:54:{s:2:"id";s:3:"127";s:8:"grant_id";s:2:"18";s:7:"user_id";s:3:"126";s:4:"name";s:24:"Le spectre de boko haram";s:6:"p_date";s:2:"70";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:8:"e_length";s:3:"60+";s:7:"logline";s:172:"
