Mohamed, Falta, Ladji, Ismaela. they seem quite fulfilled but aware of what they have been through. Lamine the teacher is also an important character in the film.";s:17:"artistic_approach";s:1918:"Artistic directorial note
Visually, the film navigates between mystical and surrealistic night scenes, punctuated by the appalling tales of children and the banality of their busy daily life. We plan to explore magical realism in this documentary to enhance our artistic creation.
Magical realism is an artistic current which "intends to offer a vision of reality renewed and broadened by taking into consideration the part of the strangeness, irrationality or mystery that it conceals. The story and the characters are anchored in reality, but the author introduces a magical or fantastic element that is not questioned in the fiction  ". Magical realism has inspired directors like Akira Kurosawa (dreams) Jean-Pierre Jeunet (Amelie from Montmartre) or Benh Zeitlin (The beasts of the sourthern wild). We didn’t find so much references in documentary, but I guess if only we push forward the research, we might be able to find some.So, when asked how to transpose these elements of magical realism to this documentary project, we thought about observing nature and using different elements, namely air, water or even earth. Our reference in the matter would be the films by Andrei Tarkovsky the mirror and the Stalker. Films through which these elements play an important role, bringing a touch that is simultaneously surreal, magical, hypnotic and enigmatic. In this project, we intend to add to these elements, a discourse and a poetic capture of images through long static takes.
Thus,the rhythm will sometimes be frenzied to emphasize the dynamism of children always in perpetual motion, sometimes posed, poetic and contemplative to represent the environment in which they live, a frozen space-time. In Kolofata, the barrier between the past, the present and the future becomes very porous. The village looks like so many other Cameroonian villages to those which already existed 50 years; 100 years ago. 
