Yaye Khadi, Mamadou’s mother, is looking kindly at the situation as they attempt the building of an ambitious community center and give a positive example to a youth tempted to Migrate. 

The film follows them in those construction and integration processes within the village of Gandiol. Will their active utopia withstand the hardships of the local realities?

Gandiol is a fishing village in northern Senegal, just before Saint Louis. On a coast dotted with palm trees, it faces the menace of an advancing sea which destroys more houses every year. Gandiol saw many young people leave, including Mamadou Dia in 2006 in a pirogue towards Spain.

Even today many young people from Gandiol envy their elders who left and returned "rich".

It is within this environment that Mamadou, returned to engage with the young people of Gandiol by setting up projects trying to fight against their departure in pirogues, and creating opportunities for them. Some remain skeptical and do not adhere to their vision, they do not understand why he wants convince them to stay.

They have their own dream of departure, one they hold dear.
Laura supports Mamadou, she also has her personal challenges in this context where she is a foreigner : her fears and doubts about the future of their family. She faces all the pressure that weighs on them every day, in the implementation of projects, the management of the community house.
After having implemented many initiatives, Mamadou and Laura are at a critical moment in their development: they are facing professional, economic and relational difficulties which will inevitably affect their future";s:22:"characters_description";s:1548:"This film is like a Sérère polyphonic song, with three Voices and a Choir

•	Mamadou, The Lead Voice

We follow Mamadou after 5 years of his return. He’s building a center of community development. How will all this impact him ? The challenges, the failures. What does returning mean to him and the people he his working with.

Sometimes Mamadou in his moments of loneliness will drive us into his utopia, his hopes and doubts. And the beautiful landscape of Gandiol and the sound will help us to get into the head of Mamadou, contrasting with the  challenges and conflict of the center.

•	Laura, The Soloist 

Laura, Mamadou’s wife, is the second voice. A Spanish woman who migrated to Senegal. She worked here, met Mamadou here, they married and she chose to commit to his project. What does it mean for her ? To integrate without disintegrating herself ? How does it impact her, her children, her couple ? Will they be able to build a post-colonial relationship ?

•	Yaye Khadi, The Rythm

The third voice, she’s the bridge between his son Mamadou and the traditional village. She is the guardian of the temple. Interviews with her and scenes will give us depth to our story and anchor it in the specific environment that is Gandiol.

