Through the character of Mamadou Dia, we will discover the situations, the characters and the challenges of social change, which is above all an individual change.

The reality of everyday situations in which we embark with him will be told through captured scenes and moments of life: my camera will follow Mamadou in his steps to move forward on his project. His team meetings, the important encounters with the village community, seeing in negotiations with authorities ...

We will Discover his difficulties and how they influence his personality. The debates and conflicts with the young people he is trying to convince. His ability to adapt to reality at the risk of losing his dream. We will film his reaction to challenges, his reintegration process.

Through Laura, I will film the interaction with Mamadou’s large family and with residents of the village, to reveal the complexity of her position, to confront perspectives, to film the process of integration. Sometimes I will isolate Mamadou and Laura to see how they manage their married life; discover them differently, in the closeness of their doubts and hopes, to perceive their fragility.

Mamadou will make us discover, the character of Yaaye Khadi, his mother; the one who advises and mediates, the bridge towards the authentic culture of the village. Her story and presence will offer moments of intimacy to Mamadou, but also a deeper sense to the life and history of this village and community

The goal is to see things from their point of view, and to follow this emotional process.

