";s:20:"letter_of_motivation";s:1988:"The New Man project has crucially developed since we presented it at different markets/funds previously, Ouaga Film Lab 2020, Fond Jeune Creation Francophone 2020, EFM DocSalon Toolbox program 2021, SDI Connecting Stories program 2021, Venice Gap-Financing Market 2021 and DocA fund 2021.
Since we had an important event that happened, even though it was always considered a possibility, with our main character. Because of his fragile health and the covid19 situation that could put him in great danger, he finally left the ghost village after 38 years. For us it’s been a great challenge to adapt to this new circumstances but in the same time a blessing in terms of creative possibilities.
This new situation forced us to rethink some ideas, concepts that it was only possible with the events that happened in the past months. 
We had the opportunity to travel back to the island and capture this new reality that right away seemed much more rich and interesting. Today we have our main character living in the village of Estancia Braz, the place that almost 40 years ago the people who left the other village, Ribeira Funda, went to live. This creates a complete new environment for our character, living among the ones that he always refused to follow. But also, to live with his sister, ironically the first one that left the village, contrary to Quirino who was the last one to do so. We are now connecting with him in this new setting but also the whole dynamic of this new place. The film become a possible metaphor about transformations. The effect of time on the places and in us but also about the transformations of these places and Quirino itself. 
Since these are recent events that happened we don’t have new written material to support it but instead we edited a 15 minute sample with new footage that allows us with this visual material to show and support these new ideas, concepts, pace, mode and intentions we want to explore in this continuing new journey.
";s:14:"representation";s:1075:"-	I have been invited to apply for Venice GAP financing market with one of my projects. I applied with THE NEW MAN trusting that the project would benefit from such respected platform which will allow us to examine the international market possibilities and collect feedback for future references.  We are now waiting for the final decision which is expected during July. However, this process allowed us to explore a couple of universal themes that would make THE NEW MAN accessible to wider audiences, such as climate change and its influence on our everyday life and mind set. Nevertheless, we understand that we are navigating slightly unfamiliar visual representations of time and space that truly special to our character, Cape Verde’s islands and their inhabitants. Our mission remains hopeful that we tell a very personal authentic story in an authentic setting that full of local cinematic punctuations and conventions to attract worldwide audiences without comprising the simplicity and complexity of our character and his unique environment and landscape.     
