on";s:19:"2021-06-25 14:59:43";s:5:"award";s:1:"0";}i:64;a:54:{s:2:"id";s:3:"401";s:8:"grant_id";s:2:"18";s:7:"user_id";s:3:"835";s:4:"name";s:25:"Standing the Test of Time";s:6:"p_date";s:2:"90";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:8:"e_length";s:3:"60+";s:7:"logline";s:124:"Becoming a teenage mother is not enough to make Taiwo Ajai-Lycett the bird with a broken wing, which cannot soar high again.";s:15:"story_structure";s:7:"not yet";s:22:"characters_description";s:7:"not yet";s:17:"artistic_approach";s:7:"not yet";s:17:"rel_status_update";s:0:"";s:20:"letter_of_motivation";s:0:"";s:14:"representation";s:0:"";s:21:"representation_upload";s:21:"2021/1621269226_1.jpg";s:16:"contracts_upload";s:0:"";s:15:"artistic_upload";s:0:"";s:13:"visual_upload";s:0:"";s:12:"project_link";s:0:"";s:16:"project_password";s:0:"";s:8:"synopsis";s:0:"";s:13:"projectBudget";s:5:"14200";s:13:"financialPlan";s:0:"";s:12:"totalSecured";s:4:"2000";s:12:"totalApplied";s:1:"0";s:11:"totalPening";s:1:"0";s:13:"BudgetDeficit";s:5:"12200";s:10:"budgetFile";s:21:"2021/1621269644_1.pdf";s:9:"proofFile";s:0:"";s:13:"contractProof";s:0:"";s:12:"ackStatement";s:0:"";s:11:"submittedBy";s:18:"Amarachukwu Iwuala";s:12:"project_role";s:9:"filmmaker";s:10:"filmmanker";s:0:"";s:8:"producer";s:0:"";s:20:"project_co_ordinator";s:0:"";s:13:"project_role2";s:0:"";s:16:"project_category";s:0:"";s:13:"project_brief";s:0:"";s:16:"project_timeline";s:1:"0";s:16:"project_describe";s:0:"";s:12:"organisation";s:0:"";s:20:"explain_organisation";s:0:"";s:15:"briefly_explain";s:0:"";s:14:"socio_economic";s:0:"";s:10:"video_link";s:0:"";s:16:"description_link";s:0:"";s:20:"description_password";s:0:"";s:15:"proposal_upload";s:0:"";s:10:"project_co";s:1:"0";s:8:"complete";s:1:"1";s:6:"status";s:1:"2";s:5:"addon";s:19:"2021-06-25 14:59:55";s:5:"award";s:1:"0";}i:65;a:54:{s:2:"id";s:3:"402";s:8:"grant_id";s:2:"18";s:7:"user_id";s:3:"721";s:4:"name";s:11:"The Lioness";s:6:"p_date";s:3:"180";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:8:"e_length";s:3:"60+";s:7:"logline";s:195:"The documentary follows a teenage girl from South Africa to India who breaks into  Bollywood. As she delves deeper into the glitz and glam, she discovers the dark underbelly of the film industry.";s:15:"story_structure";s:1941:"The story is about an African-Indian/Indian-African girl. Practicing Ubuntu, that nebulous concept of common humanity and oneness, “I am because you are”, belonging to a collective, unselfish Revering our forefathers. She was cognizant of representing her family's name, and all that it encompassed when she left Africa with a dream. This was her only support for what could be a crazy story. 
Being a part of apartheid South Africa and the impact it had on the Indian community too, added another layer of who she was, her very identity, and the choices she would ultimately make in India.

The first 2 episodes are going to explore her journey from South Africa to India; becoming a known face in India. We will see how a simple girl from Africa makes it to the top of the Indian film circuit; how she navigates her way through the immoral world; infested by the dark underworld, powerful cabals; debauchery, sex, and drugs, nepotism, and patriarchy.

The second 2 episodes are about her journey from the current day onwards....in pursuit of peace, purpose, and meaning. In this latter part, after the sad demise of her beloved father, we will see her return to India on a quest for self-discovery. The backdrop is glamorous and beautiful; while we accompany her on her path meeting with fascinating characters. From politicians to movie stars; engaging and enjoying adventurous activities, we see her growth and evolution.

The expanse and vastness of the worlds she occupies; the intense glamour against the distinct underbelly, managing the antagonized similarities and the great differences in a quest to survive; to understand how she navigated her way, to become triumphant, overcoming hurdle after hurdle in what seemed like an endless ocean of trauma.

She would use her traditions, heritage, and culture of the continent to feed her strength, make her own set of rules and ultimately achieve what she set her mind to.";s:22:"characters_description";s:1969:"Tarina Patel, the central character of the docu-series, is the first girl from the continent of Africa who broke into the Indian film industry. She belongs to the Indian community from South Africa, and grows up in a society that holds on to a culture it brought with itself some 160 years ago. Early on, Tarina’s grandmother taught her the importance of sexual abstinence before marriage and what it requires to be the ideal Indian girl.

With this moral compass embedded in her, Tarina, embarks on her international life, in her teens. While at medical school in India, she is spotted by talent scouts and offered modeling jobs.  Soon she finds herself totally immersed in showbiz as if she was destined for it. She appears in over 100 TV commercials and on countless billboards all over the country. After learning the local language, she forays into the Bollywood film industry; starring in over a dozen global blockbuster Indian films. 

Barely out of her teens, Tarina was already living the life many can only dream of: flying first class and in private jets, living in 5-star hotel suites around the world, shooting huge campaigns and earning a ton of money. However, what actually was going on behind the scenes was the complete antithesis of this world of glamour. In fact it was a dark world entrenched in deceit, drugs and debauchery. And Tarina was right in the middle of it. 

She gets a peek into the Bollywood promiscuity and is offered the casting couch. On the one hand, she has to maintain this perfect image that she had so well-curated and on the other, she would cry inside because someone regularly violated her sense of morals. She was not just representing herself but also the name of her family, the community she came from, her culture and her traditions. She drew strength from her roots and this very world taught her to be brave and courageous. She wanted to achieve her goals but on her own terms; with a clean conscience. 


";s:17:"artistic_approach";s:1580:" 
THE LIONESS is going to be a 4 part documentary feature, with each part running between ca. 45 minutes. The narrative will be from the view of Tarina, but different perspectives will be shown from directors, producers, designers, and co-actors, etc. 

Tarina will retrace her journey– visiting the places studios and meeting the people she has worked with in the past. This way the audience will get to travel with her and immerse themselves in the world Tarina works and moves. Though real-life scenes will be captured in 'a documentary' style including interview sessions with Tarina, there is scope for re-contructing a few scenes that have occurred in the past. To construct the past events we will also incorporate footage from past TVCs, films and pictures from print media campaigns. New and fresh material will be shot of Tarina's role as an actor possibly against the green screen and edited with archive material. 

The aesthetics and shooting style will incorporate glamorous high key lighting. We plan to shoot with either the Arri Alexa Mini which can be easily rigged on a gimbal or the Sony Venice which is known for its low light sensitivity. 

We will also shoot TVCs for the brands she has worked with in the past. We will focus on beautiful close-ups to give an intimate feel as well as picturesque aerial and long shots of cities and cutaways. We will have photoshoots with one of the top photographers in Bollywood. Also, we will visit the studios at Film City and possibly place her in already constructed sets and shoot B-roll and MOTs/stand ups.";s:17:"rel_status_update";s:0:"";s:20:"letter_of_motivation";s:0:"";s:14:"representation";s:0:"";s:21:"representation_upload";s:21:"2021/1621192427_1.pdf";s:16:"contracts_upload";s:0:"";s:15:"artistic_upload";s:0:"";s:13:"visual_upload";s:0:"";s:12:"project_link";s:0:"";s:16:"project_password";s:0:"";s:8:"synopsis";s:0:"";s:13:"projectBudget";s:6:"326231";s:13:"financialPlan";s:0:"";s:12:"totalSecured";s:5:"15000";s:12:"totalApplied";s:6:"150000";s:11:"totalPening";s:1:"0";s:13:"BudgetDeficit";s:6:"311231";s:10:"budgetFile";s:21:"2021/1621192531_1.pdf";s:9:"proofFile";s:0:"";s:13:"contractProof";s:0:"";s:12:"ackStatement";s:0:"";s:11:"submittedBy";s:19:"Tarina Patel-Sharma";s:12:"project_role";s:8:"producer";s:10:"filmmanker";s:0:"";s:8:"producer";s:0:"";s:20:"project_co_ordinator";s:0:"";s:13:"project_role2";s:0:"";s:16:"project_category";s:0:"";s:13:"project_brief";s:0:"";s:16:"project_timeline";s:1:"0";s:16:"project_describe";s:0:"";s:12:"organisation";s:0:"";s:20:"explain_organisation";s:0:"";s:15:"briefly_explain";s:0:"";s:14:"socio_economic";s:0:"";s:10:"video_link";s:0:"";s:16:"description_link";s:0:"";s:20:"description_password";s:0:"";s:15:"proposal_upload";s:0:"";s:10:"project_co";s:1:"0";s:8:"complete";s:1:"1";s:6:"status";s:1:"2";s:5:"addon";s:19:"2021-06-25 15:00:08";s:5:"award";s:1:"0";}i:66;a:54:{s:2:"id";s:3:"403";s:8:"grant_id";s:2:"18";s:7:"user_id";s:3:"849";s:4:"name";s:18:"And who will cook?";s:6:"p_date";s:2:"90";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:8:"e_length";s:3:"60+";s:7:"logline";s:198:"A resilience story of Patricia, who does not give up dreamin