Indepth research that will focus on geographical outlook, historical background, traditional politics & governance of Yoruba kingdoms from pre-colonial era all through colonial era. Sociocultural lifestyles, institutional norms, conventions & customs, as well as cultural exchanges & practices will be extensively emphasized in the series documentary.  

It will serially focus on selected and researched historical, Industrial, culture & tourism-oriented Yoruba towns: Ikeja, Badagary (slave trade), Ile Ife(Yoruba Orgin), Akure, Ondo, Owo, Olokola (Bitumen Deposit), Agege, Araromi Obu (Rubber Plantation), Ikogosi (Warm Spring), Oke Igbo (Antiquities Tourist Centre), Abeokuta (Olumo Hills) & Idanre (Idanre Hills)    ";s:22:"characters_description";s:386:"Pre-interviews and interviews will be conducted for a few selected individuals that can contribute to the stories by the virtues of their status and experiences.  
   
