The second chapter shows the current wave of mass migration whereby African youth with untapped potential are leaving in their thousands to look for a better life. This time young people are fleeing various post-colonial challenges in their countries. We follow a boat captain, Captain Abdourahmane Diop who facilitates the irregular migration these African youth are taking. 

The third and final chapter takes place in a seaside Catholic Mission in Nouadhibou headed by Bishop Martin Harpe. From time to time, the wreckages of boats carrying irregular migrants wash up on the shore near his mission. Not knowing whether the bodies are those of Christians, Muslims or non-believers, the local population is forbidden to touch them. Bishop Harpe has started a cemetery for these forgotten people as he does the work of giving last rites.
";s:22:"characters_description";s:965:"The Four major characters in this film are very interesting characters.

