anks among three countries in the world deemed utterly prone to harsh effects of global warming , as the global warming threat intensify, it becoming crystal clear that  Sierra Leone is at great risk of impending dangers if steps are not immediately taken to robustly respond to potential disasters. While in other countries environmental threats are hinged mainly on industrialization, Sierra Leone’s situation is blamed entirely on human factors such as deforestation, illegal land grabbing, take into consideration the disasters that have occurred in Sierra Leone  On August 14, 2017, a devastating landslide ripped through Sierra Leone's capital city, Freetown. this caused millions of dollars of destruction and damaged to buildings, infrastructure, and reported loss of morethan a thousand lives
