'Unmasking' seeks to explore the peace that existed, the clashes that ensued and the resolution reached.

We will explore the ritual of the Ibegwu festival, which invokes an ancestral spirit who comes out in Egwu Affia masquerade. The Muslim Umars, in a bid to convert the Ibegwu worshippers, begin a radical Islamic crusade, which provokes retaliation by the latter, who accuse them of desecration and also of encroaching on their land, leading to a protracted conflict.

Several casualties result, until the Gago of Odo (the Chief), calls a truce and summons all parties to a dialogue, which eventually brings peace and tolerance back to the community.

