(the sample should be subtitled by next week)";s:20:"letter_of_motivation";s:2000:"The subject of the returning migrants has preoccupied me as part of a process to change the narrative on migration. The return is both joyful and difficult, bringing us face to face with the reality of change, the people and places we have found again, in a new light. 
The one who returns has also become someone else, even a stranger in his own home, he will have to change again to find a place in the society to which he is returning.
This film was born out of the desire to tell a modern African story, an example of a young man who chose to return home after years of hiding to make a commitment, despite all possible difficulties.

The desire to give a voice to young people like Mamadou, to expose his dream and the obstacles he faces, a way to accompany his quest with the production of images, his desire to renew the discourse and to recreate the relationship to oneself and to others.

Through Mamadou, I wish to hear other voices around him, those of Laura, of the young people of the village, of Yaaye Khady and of the village of Gandiol.  Like a Serere polyphonic song, where the singer is surrounded by a troop of choruses that respond to his phrasing, sometimes cutting it, covering it and intertwining it as if to weave a speech with different meanings, different rhythms and melodies!

The desire of a "choral film" to sketch a contemporary tableau, that of a generation committed to building its dreams, which does not resign itself to difficulties, which opens up paths of possibilities.

My trusting relationship with Mamadou and Laura allows me to film very closely and above all to live the hopes and fears in this adventure, to observe from the inside.

To film the process of reintegration of this migrant, to show that the journey does not stop for the one who dreams and returns home, the process of change impacts first of all the one who commits himself to it in order to transform the world, without being sure to succeed.Making cinema to transform reality.";s:14:"representation";s:1866:"With Doxandem, the dream chasers, Saliou Sarr highlights one of the most important societal issues of our time. Subtly, this film finds itself at the crossroads of all these major themes that are currently dominating the debate on migration. It can therefore only be a valuable object for an audience that is too often exposed to a discourse devoid of nuances on the issue of migration. For today, it is no longer about stories, still less about adventure or Odysseus. Everything is reduced to unfathomable statistics.

By choosing an aesthetic approach, through cinema, to such a subject, Saliou Sarr becomes a witness of his time, as well as the spokesman for a youth whose voice is too rarely heard without being altered, and invites the spectator into his gaze. 

The project has just began its production. Our first shooting took place March of 2021. Additional shootings during summer and the fall will unfold. We wish to accompany that process while still looking for additional finances. 

Provided that those steps are successful and accomplished on time, we wish to complete the film for a release by the second trimester of 2022. This process had been boosted by the success we encountered in many development Lab : The Ouaga Film Lab where we were awarded 3 prices including a participation to the latest IDFA Forum, The Miradas Docs Lab where we were recipient of the Durban Film Mart award where we are set to participate in July. 

Led by our co-production partners STEPS, and with the support of the different partners of the film, this distribution strategy will be based on the integration of this project into the documentary collection Generation Africa. Its momentum will be reinforced by the submission and expected participation of the work at major film festivals around the world as well as through effective digital communication.
